# frontend — Angular 21 SPA

This is `movie-finder-frontend` (`frontend/`) — the user interface for Movie Finder.
GitHub repo: `aharbii/movie-finder-frontend` · Tracker: `aharbii/movie-finder`

## What this submodule does

Angular 21 SPA: user types a natural-language film description → SSE stream shows candidates → user confirms → follow-up Q&A chat.

- **SSE:** `EventSource` consumes the FastAPI `/stream` endpoint
- **nginx:** serves the production build and reverse-proxies API calls
- **Runtime env injection:** `docker-entrypoint.sh` injects config at container start — no build-time secrets

## Key source layout

```
src/
├── app/
│   ├── features/
│   │   ├── chat/          # Q&A chat interface
│   │   └── search/        # Film search + SSE candidates
│   ├── core/              # Auth, HTTP interceptors, guards
│   └── shared/            # Shared UI components
angular.json               # Build + test config
nginx.conf.template        # Production nginx (env-var substituted at runtime)
docker-entrypoint.sh       # Injects runtime env
Dockerfile                 # Multi-stage: node builder → nginx runtime
proxy.conf.js              # Dev server proxy → backend:8000
```

## Stack

- Angular 21, TypeScript 5.9
- Standalone components only (no NgModules)
- Signals for all reactive state
- SSE via `EventSource` (wrapped in facade service)
- Tests: Vitest
- Linting: ESLint 9 flat config + Prettier

## Quality checks (all run through Make — never raw npm)

```bash
make lint
make typecheck
make test
make test-coverage
make pre-commit
make check    # typecheck + lint + test-coverage in one shot
```

## Non-negotiables

- Standalone components only — no NgModules ever
- Signals for state — no `BehaviorSubject` for component state
- No `any` — use `unknown` + narrowing
- Components never call `HttpClient` or `EventSource` directly — always through a facade service
- No `console.log()` in production code
- Never `git add -A`, never `--no-verify`, Conventional Commits

